2917. FROM FRANZ Rmus A SPRINZENSTEIN.

Breslau MS. Rehd. 254. 142. Tiibingen. EE2. 114. 17 March 1534.

[An original letter, autograph throughout.

Francisous Ritius of Sprinzcnstein was the elder son of Paul Rieius (see Ep. 548. 15n) and brother of Jeroine Ricius (see Ep. 2131 inti-od). From this letter it seems that he was attached to the court of Ferdinand. In Feb. Ferdinand had sent him from hinsbruck to confer with Duke Philip of Psalz-Neuburg. who in 1532 had been appointed governor of W'urtenibcrg. At the tirne of writing he was at Tubingen awaiting the return of the Duke. From 1. 66 it appears that he had reeently been in Freiburg. From 'the opening of the letter it may further be inferred that while at Innsbruek he had received a letter from Erasmus (not extant) replying to a letter of his own (also not extant) written from that place. In his previous letter he had mentioned the death of John Francis Pie-0 of Mirandula (†15 Oct. 1533); that letter, therefore, must have been written after that dato. He was sent on embassics to Constantinople, 1530, and later to Spain. In Mameranus' Cataloyus familiae totius aulae Caesareae (Cologne, 1550) he appears in the list of Ferdinand's Consilium ecclesiastici as Provost οἱ Trent.
